  "number": 40,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/40",
  "title": "0.0.1 Roadmap",
  "body": "We aim for a 0.0.1 release.\n\nWe have a [0.0.1 milestone](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/milestones/0.0.1). This issue was made to easily track and comment on the 0.0.1 roadmap.\n## Goals\n\nBeing able to reproduce the [instant search demo](http://demos.algolia.com/instant-search-demo/) using instantsearch.js.\n\nGet CSE and integrators (magento, wordpress) to use and give us feedback on the instantsearch.js API.\n\nThe library should be hosted on jsDelivr. Even if we are at the prototype state where we will break the API.\n\n[Check the 0.0.1 milestone](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/milestones/0.0.1) on github to get a good idea of what's required for the release.\n## New widgets\n\nHere are all the widgets and related issues we need to do for 0.0.1:\n- [x] hits\n- [x] pagination #13\n- [x] multipleChoiceList #42 \n- [x] menu #49 \n- [x] toggle #41\n- [x] slider #11 \n- [x] stats #12 \n- [x] indexSelector #38 \n- [x] urlSync #17 \n\nSee all the [new widget](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues?q=is%3Aopen+label%3A%22new+widget%22+milestone%3A0.0.1) related issues for 0.0.1.\n\nWe should also make sure that we document each widget API in the project readme (for now), like we did for the first widgets.\n## Bug fixes and enhancements\n\n[Check the 0.0.1 milestone](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/milestones/0.0.1) to see other remaining bugs and enhancements we should do.\n",
